WEBVTT

00:01.120 --> 00:04.830
Whoa.
A banana hanger.

00:04.830 --> 00:06.170
Did we win
the lottery?

00:06.170 --> 00:08.000
Now that we've been
a two-income family for a while,

00:08.000 --> 00:10.580
we can finally replace
the stuff that's falling apart

00:10.580 --> 00:12.250
and enjoy
a few luxuries.

00:12.250 --> 00:14.290
Oh, yeah. Those 'nanas
gonna be heck-a-ripe.

00:14.290 --> 00:15.290
Mm-hmm.

00:15.290 --> 00:16.420
It is nice not worrying

00:16.420 --> 00:17.960
about every dollar
we spend, for once.

00:17.960 --> 00:20.170
Whoa.

00:20.170 --> 00:22.000
New can opener.
That's right!

00:22.000 --> 00:24.790
Goodbye, old can opener
that only opens cans halfway

00:24.790 --> 00:26.880
so you have to pry the lid open
with a knife.

00:26.880 --> 00:29.000
Goodbye, knife we ruined
opening cans.

00:29.000 --> 00:30.170
And look,
we finally have art

00:30.170 --> 00:32.040
that wasn't made
by the kids.

00:32.040 --> 00:33.460
Say hello
to the painting

00:33.460 --> 00:35.580
that says "family"
in five languages.

00:35.580 --> 00:36.960
I love it.
Let's hang it.

00:36.960 --> 00:38.420
You'll have to do it
without me.

00:38.420 --> 00:39.670
I have to go into work
to talk to Whitney.

00:39.670 --> 00:41.460
It's Sunday.

00:41.460 --> 00:43.170
And why do you have to go
in the office to meet with her?

00:43.170 --> 00:44.460
Isn't she always
on speakerphone?

00:44.460 --> 00:47.380
Yeah. It's dumb.
This whole job is dumb.

00:47.380 --> 00:48.580
You used to like
party planning.

00:48.580 --> 00:49.580
For a second.

00:49.580 --> 00:51.040
It was a fun way
to make money,

00:51.040 --> 00:52.170
and I liked
people that I hate

00:52.170 --> 00:54.210
telling me
what a good job I did.

00:54.210 --> 00:56.460
But now
it's crushing my soul.

00:56.460 --> 00:57.790
Guess that's
the price you pay

00:57.790 --> 00:59.210
if you want
to hang your bananas.

00:59.210 --> 01:00.830
Gross. Leave that talk
in the bedroom.

01:02.540 --> 01:04.620
Thanks for working so hard.
It means a lot to your family.

01:04.620 --> 01:08.420
And your familia,
famille,

01:08.420 --> 01:11.040
famiglia,
and your mischpokhe.

01:14.620 --> 01:15.670
What is that?

01:15.670 --> 01:17.710
Nothing.

01:17.710 --> 01:19.250
Are you wearing
a bracelet?

01:19.250 --> 01:20.710
You're gonna be late
for work.

01:20.710 --> 01:23.880
Are you auditioning to be
the cute one in a boy band?

01:23.880 --> 01:25.250
I don't want
to talk about it!

01:25.250 --> 01:27.790
Katie: Katie, just let the guy
wear a bracelet.

01:27.790 --> 01:28.790
You're not going to, are you?

01:28.790 --> 01:29.790
[ Chuckles ] No.

01:33.460 --> 01:37.080
♪♪

01:37.080 --> 01:39.790
Hey, Oliver, you want to play
the Game of Life?

01:39.790 --> 01:41.540
No.
You guys play.

01:41.540 --> 01:43.380
I already lost
the real version.

01:44.670 --> 01:46.540
What's wrong?

01:46.540 --> 01:48.500
My dream of getting into Harvard
is officially dead.

01:48.500 --> 01:50.710
I can't dance,
so I plan on padding my résumé

01:50.710 --> 01:52.330
with some BS volunteer work.

01:52.330 --> 01:53.670
That sounds like
a good idea.

01:53.670 --> 01:55.290
But look at me.

01:55.290 --> 01:57.330
I can't plant trees,

01:57.330 --> 02:00.080
deliver meals,
build habitats.

02:00.080 --> 02:01.380
All I can do
is sit.

02:01.380 --> 02:02.790
My life is over.

02:02.790 --> 02:04.460
You have lots
going for you.

02:04.460 --> 02:06.250
You're ambitious,
your grades are great.

02:06.250 --> 02:07.750
Plus,
you're a sophomore.

02:07.750 --> 02:09.620
You have time
to build up your résumé.

02:09.620 --> 02:11.750
You want to feel better,
look at Taylor.

02:11.750 --> 02:12.830
Yeah, yeah!

02:12.830 --> 02:14.500
She's the one
that should be depressed.

02:14.500 --> 02:16.380
She's graduating
this year,

02:16.380 --> 02:18.500
and the girl's got
nothing going on.

02:18.500 --> 02:21.500
And even if she does
somehow go to college,

02:21.500 --> 02:23.790
Mom and Dad gave her
a long list of life skills,

02:23.790 --> 02:25.920
and she can't even
fill the car with gas.

02:25.920 --> 02:27.710
That's not true.
I filled it.

02:27.710 --> 02:33.120
♪♪

02:33.120 --> 02:34.750
I hate that list!

02:34.750 --> 02:36.000
I'm never gonna survive
outside this house

02:36.000 --> 02:38.040
if I can't do anything!

02:39.830 --> 02:41.170
This is what happens

02:41.170 --> 02:43.540
when everyone gets
participation trophies.

02:45.000 --> 02:46.750
Katie.
Hi, Kevin.

02:46.750 --> 02:48.210
What kind of
stupid ice sculpture

02:48.210 --> 02:49.790
do I have to order
for this dumb party?

02:49.790 --> 02:51.290
Whitney cannot see you
like this.

02:51.290 --> 02:52.790
You are too underdressed
for the office.

02:52.790 --> 02:54.960
I know she has the place
wired with cameras,

02:54.960 --> 02:57.330
but I've got it covered.

02:57.330 --> 03:00.500
When she calls in,
I'll be sitting at my desk,

03:00.500 --> 03:02.250
wearing this blazer.

03:02.250 --> 03:04.580
But Whitney will know
because --

03:04.580 --> 03:05.710
Whitney:
Hello, Katie.

03:05.710 --> 03:07.880
Hi, Whitney!

03:07.880 --> 03:10.000
Why are you talking into
a speakerphone?

03:12.420 --> 03:14.790
You know, I'm not sure
how much time you allocate

03:14.790 --> 03:16.210
for getting ready
in the morning,

03:16.210 --> 03:17.710
but you might want
to double it.

03:17.710 --> 03:20.670
In my defense, I have worked
here for more than a year,

03:20.670 --> 03:23.210
and this is the first time
that I have laid eyes on you.

03:23.210 --> 03:25.000
I suppose
that would explain

03:25.000 --> 03:28.170
Kevin's lack of
professional attire, as well.

03:28.170 --> 03:30.000
You bought this
for me.

03:30.000 --> 03:31.790
As a razz,
Kevin.

03:31.790 --> 03:34.380
Now, I'm in town
for only one week,

03:34.380 --> 03:38.210
and I'm trusting you
to throw a very special party

03:38.210 --> 03:40.500
for my
most important client.

03:40.500 --> 03:41.580
Martha Stewart?

03:41.580 --> 03:44.580
Better.
My favorite nephew, Joshua.

03:44.580 --> 03:45.790
Okay.

03:45.790 --> 03:47.880
Well, what kind of ice sculpture
would he like?

03:47.880 --> 03:50.170
No, no. Eh, the party's not
for Joshua.

03:50.170 --> 03:52.670
He wants
to throw a party for Lizzie.

03:52.670 --> 03:54.000
And Lizzie is?

03:54.000 --> 03:55.380
His iguana.

03:55.380 --> 03:57.420
I'm throwing a party
for a reptile?

03:57.420 --> 03:58.790
Of course!

03:58.790 --> 04:00.500
I once threw a party

04:00.500 --> 04:03.580
for Bitsy Wellington's
favorite purse.

04:03.580 --> 04:05.210
Steely Dan played.
It was magical.

04:06.080 --> 04:08.170
Oh, Katie.

04:08.170 --> 04:10.250
[ Sighs ]

04:10.250 --> 04:12.210
I have so much
to teach you.

04:16.120 --> 04:17.500
Is this
going to end soon?

04:17.500 --> 04:20.080
This is more eye contact
than I keep with my husband.

04:21.170 --> 04:23.040
I'm counting on you,
Katie.

04:23.040 --> 04:24.580
Come on, you.

04:24.580 --> 04:26.250
As long as you're wearing
your ditch-digging clothes,

04:26.250 --> 04:27.290
come to my house.

04:27.290 --> 04:29.460
I have to move
my animal cemetery.

04:29.460 --> 04:31.710
I'm putting in
a pool.

04:34.710 --> 04:37.540
Am I actually throwing a party
for a Westport lizard?

04:37.540 --> 04:38.790
Uh-huh.

04:38.790 --> 04:40.460
Whitney:
Kevin! Now!

04:42.000 --> 04:44.540
Thank you, Kevin.
For what?

04:44.540 --> 04:48.290
For showing me
that as bad as my life is,

04:48.290 --> 04:49.540
yours is worse.

04:49.540 --> 04:53.120
♪♪

04:56.540 --> 04:58.380
♪♪

04:58.380 --> 05:00.580
And the craziest part is,

05:00.580 --> 05:02.580
it's not even
the iguana's birthday.

05:02.580 --> 05:05.170
It's a party,
"just because"!

05:05.170 --> 05:06.830
[ Scoffs ]
You should quit.

05:06.830 --> 05:08.920
I thought about it.
A lot.

05:08.920 --> 05:10.960
I have a whole quitting fantasy
worked out in my head.

05:10.960 --> 05:13.000
All I need
is a boom box --

05:13.000 --> 05:14.790
A baseball bat --
And an industrial fan.

05:14.790 --> 05:17.120
Yeah, we've heard this before.
Why don't you just do it?

05:17.120 --> 05:18.920
Well, Greg's happy

05:18.920 --> 05:20.380
because now, with my salary,

05:20.380 --> 05:22.170
we're finally able
to put some money aside.

05:22.170 --> 05:23.380
Money aside?

05:23.380 --> 05:25.080
Is that something
the poors do?

05:25.080 --> 05:26.750
Like family game nights
and voting?

05:26.750 --> 05:29.880
And Greg is going through
something right now.

05:29.880 --> 05:31.080
What do you mean?

05:31.080 --> 05:32.540
He's started wearing
a leather bracelet.

05:32.540 --> 05:34.290
How fun.
Oh! Cool.

05:34.290 --> 05:35.460
That is fun.

05:35.460 --> 05:37.620
I see you nudging each other
under the table.

05:37.620 --> 05:38.960
Uh --

05:38.960 --> 05:40.460
No wife should have to
go through this.

05:40.460 --> 05:41.670
This is
very upsetting,

05:41.670 --> 05:43.380
but maybe he's just
trying something new.

05:43.380 --> 05:45.750
Yeah, like when
you started saying "Peace out."

05:45.750 --> 05:48.330
You tried it, we ignored it,
and then it went away.

05:48.330 --> 05:49.420
And you should do
the same thing with Greg.

05:49.420 --> 05:50.880
She's right.
You only need to worry

05:50.880 --> 05:51.880
if it starts
to escalate,

05:51.880 --> 05:52.750
then you shut it down.

05:52.750 --> 05:53.880
[ Cellphone chimes ]

05:53.880 --> 05:54.920
Ugh. Gotta go.

05:54.920 --> 05:56.460
Lizzie's tail fell off,

05:56.460 --> 05:58.120
so we're meeting about ways
to hide it for pictures.

05:58.120 --> 05:59.330
Catch you
on the flip-side.

05:59.330 --> 06:00.670
Stop it.
No.

06:00.670 --> 06:01.670
[ Scoffs ]

06:01.670 --> 06:03.880
♪♪

06:03.880 --> 06:05.750
What are we
gonna do today?

06:05.750 --> 06:07.830
We're gonna help cheer up
Taylor and Oliver.

06:07.830 --> 06:09.380
They're two white kids
in America.

06:09.380 --> 06:10.670
What do they have
to be sad about?

06:10.670 --> 06:12.080
Stand down,
Franklin.

06:12.080 --> 06:13.420
This isn't
your podcast.

06:13.420 --> 06:14.330
[ Sighs ]

06:14.330 --> 06:15.500
We need
to help them.

06:15.500 --> 06:17.460
What do you think
would cheer them up?

06:17.460 --> 06:19.250
What about we --
Can't be
the movie "Soapdish."

06:19.250 --> 06:22.330
Sally Field is
an American treasure.

06:25.120 --> 06:26.580
There are other ways,
Franklin!

06:26.580 --> 06:29.880
♪♪

06:29.880 --> 06:31.210
[ Knock on door ]

06:31.210 --> 06:32.250
Hey, Taylor.

06:33.250 --> 06:34.960
Franklin does
great impressions.

06:34.960 --> 06:36.290
You want
to see one?

06:41.670 --> 06:42.880
[ Exhales sharply ]

06:42.880 --> 06:43.750
[ Raspy voice ]
Did you eat?

06:43.750 --> 06:45.040
Did you eat?

06:45.040 --> 06:46.830
Did you eat?
Did you eat?

06:46.830 --> 06:49.080
[ Laughs ]

06:49.080 --> 06:50.670
Who is that
supposed to be?

06:50.670 --> 06:52.580
[ Normal voice ]
My Aunt Linda.
That is spot-on.

06:52.580 --> 06:54.250
It's like
she's in the room.

06:54.250 --> 06:55.580
Do your
Uncle Al next.

06:55.580 --> 06:56.830
Linda!

06:56.830 --> 06:59.080
The help
is stealing from us!

06:59.080 --> 07:01.170
♪♪

07:01.170 --> 07:04.290
[ Shamisen music plays ]

07:04.290 --> 07:13.290
♪♪

07:13.290 --> 07:15.420
[ As Inigo Montoya ]
My name is Inigo Montoya.

07:15.420 --> 07:17.420
You killed my father.
Prepare to die.

07:17.420 --> 07:19.040
[ As Vizzini ]
Inconceivable.

07:19.040 --> 07:20.580
You keep using
that word.

07:20.580 --> 07:23.080
I do not think it means
what you think it means.

07:24.170 --> 07:25.210
[ Laughs ]

07:25.210 --> 07:26.380
Bleh! Bleh!

07:26.380 --> 07:27.790
[ Clicks tongue ]

07:27.790 --> 07:29.080
[ Blows raspberry ]

07:29.080 --> 07:30.750
Bleh! Bleh!
[ Chuckles ]

07:34.210 --> 07:35.830
[ Normal voice ]
Nothing worked.

07:35.830 --> 07:37.540
What do we do now?

07:37.540 --> 07:39.210
[ Normal voice ] When my mom
had a bad case of the sadsies,

07:39.210 --> 07:40.460
the only thing
that helped her

07:40.460 --> 07:42.000
was talking to the counselor
at her church.

07:42.000 --> 07:43.880
Of course.
Good idea, Franklin.

07:43.880 --> 07:45.420
Time to
get God involved.

07:45.420 --> 07:47.920
Religion can be very helpful
when used as a tool,

07:47.920 --> 07:49.170
but when
it's a crutch --

07:49.170 --> 07:51.080
Not your podcast,
Franklin.

07:51.080 --> 07:53.210
♪♪

07:53.210 --> 07:54.790
Katie: This is
the most ridiculous party

07:54.790 --> 07:55.920
I've ever had to throw.

07:55.920 --> 07:58.330
I don't know how much longer
I can do this.

07:58.330 --> 08:00.040
You are the strongest person
I know,

08:00.040 --> 08:02.170
and not just because
you always open jars for me.

08:02.170 --> 08:03.250
Emotionally.

08:03.250 --> 08:06.170
You put up with a lot,
but remember,

08:06.170 --> 08:07.920
you're really good
at what you do,

08:07.920 --> 08:09.000
and everyone in town
knows it.

08:10.290 --> 08:11.960
Thank you.

08:11.960 --> 08:14.120
I appreciate tha--

08:15.880 --> 08:18.580
Are you wearing
bacon socks?

08:18.580 --> 08:20.670
No.

08:20.670 --> 08:22.000
Okay.

08:22.000 --> 08:23.500
I let
the bracelet go.

08:23.500 --> 08:25.080
I didn't say a word...

08:25.080 --> 08:26.170
to your face.

08:26.170 --> 08:27.620
But now
it's escalating,

08:27.620 --> 08:29.330
and I know
you don't want to talk about it,

08:29.330 --> 08:30.380
but you and I both know

08:30.380 --> 08:33.080
that there is bacon
on your socks.

08:33.080 --> 08:34.620
What the hell
is going on?

08:34.620 --> 08:36.880
I don't know.

08:36.880 --> 08:39.000
It kind of started after
Professor Casey passed away.

08:39.000 --> 08:40.880
He got tenure
the same week that I was hired.

08:40.880 --> 08:42.210
For the last 10 years,

08:42.210 --> 08:43.960
I've watched him do
the exact same thing

08:43.960 --> 08:45.960
until he died
at his desk,

08:45.960 --> 08:48.250
and now I have tenure.

08:48.250 --> 08:51.040
And I don't know,
it got me thinking...

08:51.040 --> 08:52.170
maybe I need
to mix things up.

08:52.170 --> 08:53.580
Figure out
who I really am.

08:53.580 --> 08:55.960
Am I bracelet guy?
Funny-sock guy?

08:55.960 --> 08:58.250
Carry-around-a-coin-
that-I-flip guy?

08:58.250 --> 08:59.040
Honey.

09:01.210 --> 09:03.880
I support
any guy you want to be.

09:04.920 --> 09:06.880
Thanks, sweetie.

09:06.880 --> 09:08.920
But if you start wearing
those glasses

09:08.920 --> 09:11.080
that are transitional
from light to dark,

09:11.080 --> 09:12.380
it's gonna be
a problem.

09:12.380 --> 09:13.960
Okay.
Yeah.

09:13.960 --> 09:18.330
♪♪

09:18.330 --> 09:19.460
[ Snake hisses ]

09:19.460 --> 09:25.790
♪♪

09:25.790 --> 09:28.540
Great party,
Katie.

09:28.540 --> 09:29.750
I sampled
the stir fry.

09:29.750 --> 09:31.040
It's delicious.

09:31.040 --> 09:33.380
Yeah.
Those are crickets.

09:33.380 --> 09:35.960
That explains
why the server was laughing.
Mm-hmm.

09:35.960 --> 09:37.580
Katie, right?
Mm-hmm.

09:37.580 --> 09:39.210
My Joshua
just told me

09:39.210 --> 09:42.080
this is the best party
Lizzie has ever had.

09:42.080 --> 09:43.960
Thank you.
I am so glad.

09:43.960 --> 09:46.540
Whitney said she worked hard
on every little detail.

09:46.540 --> 09:48.380
You are so lucky
to have a boss like her

09:48.380 --> 09:49.960
who does
all the heavy lifting.

09:49.960 --> 09:51.580
"Heavy lifting"?

09:51.580 --> 09:53.290
But she's not
even here.

09:53.290 --> 09:54.580
That's because
she's such a star.

09:54.580 --> 09:57.500
She knew she would distract
from Lizzie on her big day.

09:57.500 --> 09:59.580
Man:
Hey, Gayle.
Oh, my God. Hi.

09:59.580 --> 10:02.000
I guess a snake
would distract from a lizard.

10:02.000 --> 10:03.330
Can you believe her?

10:03.330 --> 10:05.880
Whitney has me plan
this absurd party --

10:05.880 --> 10:07.790
which I nailed,
by the way --

10:07.790 --> 10:09.790
and then steals
my thank-you.

10:09.790 --> 10:11.830
I can't wait
'til she goes back to New York.

10:11.830 --> 10:13.580
She's not going back.

10:13.580 --> 10:15.790
She's staying
in Westport.
What?

10:15.790 --> 10:18.120
Yeah, I heard her on
the phone while I was
giving her a spray tan.

10:18.120 --> 10:20.580
[ Sighs ]
I can't do this anymore.

10:20.580 --> 10:21.750
The money's great,

10:21.750 --> 10:23.540
but you can't put a price
on my dignity.

10:23.540 --> 10:24.960
Mm.

10:24.960 --> 10:27.210
The satay is delicious.

10:29.040 --> 10:30.500
Not for humans,
right?

10:30.500 --> 10:31.710
Right.

10:32.750 --> 10:36.040
♪♪

10:38.380 --> 10:41.330
Whitney,
I worked my ass off

10:41.330 --> 10:42.750
putting that party together.

10:42.750 --> 10:44.120
It's bad enough
that I'm --

10:44.120 --> 10:45.880
Not getting the recognition
you deserve.

10:47.330 --> 10:48.580
That's why I'm giving you
a promotion,

10:48.580 --> 10:50.580
which comes with
a very nice raise.

10:50.580 --> 10:51.670
[ Clicks tongue ]

10:51.670 --> 10:54.000
If you think a raise
and a promotion

10:54.000 --> 10:56.460
are enough
to keep me around...

10:56.460 --> 10:58.080
you're right.

10:58.080 --> 11:00.880
Turns out
my dignity does have a price.

11:00.880 --> 11:02.500
Now,
if you'll excuse me,

11:02.500 --> 11:04.790
I have someone coming
to give me a foot massage.

11:04.790 --> 11:07.170
Oh, the masseuse cancelled.
I thought I told you.

11:07.170 --> 11:08.830
You did.

11:08.830 --> 11:10.460
Now go get
the lotion, Kevin.

11:10.460 --> 11:15.290
♪♪

11:18.540 --> 11:21.580
♪♪

11:21.580 --> 11:23.380
So, Whitney just took
all the credit for the party?

11:23.380 --> 11:24.790
Yes.

11:24.790 --> 11:27.000
I should have grabbed
a boom box,

11:27.000 --> 11:30.580
a baseball bat,
and an industrial fan and quit.

11:30.580 --> 11:32.710
Now I'm just like you.

11:32.710 --> 11:34.170
How so?

11:34.170 --> 11:36.540
You accepted tenure,
now you're stuck at your job.

11:36.540 --> 11:39.000
I took the promotion,
and now I'm stuck at mine.

11:40.330 --> 11:41.620
So what
if I hate my job?

11:41.620 --> 11:43.040
Everyone does.

11:43.040 --> 11:45.710
[ Sighs ]
I got to get to bed.

11:45.710 --> 11:47.790
I have to oversee
all the events this week,

11:47.790 --> 11:50.330
starting with tomorrow's
"Barbecue and Botox" party.

11:50.330 --> 11:51.380
Ooh.

11:56.580 --> 11:57.670
[ Hat thuds ]

11:57.670 --> 11:58.670
I can't.

11:58.670 --> 11:59.670
[ Glass thuds ]

11:59.670 --> 12:03.040
♪♪

12:03.040 --> 12:06.380
You must be
Taylor and Oliver.

12:06.380 --> 12:09.210
Franklin tells me you've been
going through something.

12:09.210 --> 12:11.500
Yeah, it's --
it's easy to feel lost

12:11.500 --> 12:12.790
in this big world,

12:12.790 --> 12:15.170
but it's important
to remember --

12:15.170 --> 12:16.620
you're not alone.

12:16.620 --> 12:18.330
Who are you?

12:18.330 --> 12:19.580
This is Eve.

12:19.580 --> 12:21.420
She's an elder
at the church my mom goes to.

12:21.420 --> 12:22.750
She helped my mom
a lot.

12:22.750 --> 12:24.080
She blinks now.

12:24.080 --> 12:25.210
I think we're good.

12:25.210 --> 12:26.960
I remember being
a pretty young girl,

12:26.960 --> 12:28.920
my whole life
ahead of me.

12:28.920 --> 12:30.790
But I always
felt unprepared

12:30.790 --> 12:33.000
and ill-equipped
for life on my own.

12:33.000 --> 12:35.000
You did?
Oh, yes.

12:35.000 --> 12:37.670
I was overwhelmed
and lost.

12:37.670 --> 12:39.960
Me, too.
So, what changed?

12:39.960 --> 12:42.080
I joined the church,
met Bob.

12:42.080 --> 12:43.380
Who's Bob?

12:43.380 --> 12:45.250
Bob owns the compound
we all live on.

12:45.250 --> 12:47.120
He's our leader
and our husband.

12:47.120 --> 12:49.250
Our husband?
Yes.

12:49.250 --> 12:51.330
Bob must take many wives
so he has enough people

12:51.330 --> 12:53.040
to take care of him
at the end of days.

12:53.040 --> 12:55.580
Then he'll reunite us
with the great leader

12:55.580 --> 12:58.250
and deliver us
to our home planet.

12:58.250 --> 12:59.710
[ Chuckles nervously ]

12:59.710 --> 13:01.960
Your mom
doesn't go to a church.

13:01.960 --> 13:03.120
She's in a cult.

13:04.330 --> 13:06.670
Ohhh.

13:06.670 --> 13:09.420
That's why Grandpa
keeps trying to kidnap us.

13:09.420 --> 13:11.170
Anna-Kat will
walk you out.

13:11.170 --> 13:13.170
Bob be with you.
And also with you.

13:13.170 --> 13:15.580
Oh.
[ Chuckles ]

13:17.250 --> 13:19.620
Oh, my God.
That was so inspiring.

13:19.620 --> 13:20.920
I feel like you're getting
the wrong message.

13:20.920 --> 13:22.420
[ Door opens ]
No.

13:22.420 --> 13:24.120
You know how my life
is screwed up compared to yours?

13:24.120 --> 13:25.750
[ Door closes ]
Well, compared to
a grown woman

13:25.750 --> 13:27.380
with pigtails
who's in a cult,

13:27.380 --> 13:28.420
I'm killing it.

13:28.420 --> 13:29.420
Ha.

13:29.420 --> 13:32.000
♪♪

13:32.000 --> 13:34.290
♪♪

13:34.290 --> 13:35.790
[ Indistinct conversations ]

13:37.120 --> 13:38.960
Thank you so much.

13:38.960 --> 13:41.040
The genius...

13:41.040 --> 13:43.750
is in the minutiae...
[ Chuckles ]

13:43.750 --> 13:46.210
...or whatever
that phrase is.

13:46.210 --> 13:47.750
[ Both chuckle ]

13:47.750 --> 13:49.040
[ Gasps ] Katie,

13:49.040 --> 13:51.790
everything
is fantastic.

13:51.790 --> 13:54.120
Well, I'd take a bow,
but you've already done that.

13:54.120 --> 13:55.420
Yes. [ Chuckles ]

13:55.420 --> 13:58.290
There's just one thing
that's bothering me.

13:58.290 --> 13:59.750
Ugh.
The bluegrass band?

13:59.750 --> 14:01.170
I know.
It's a lot of harmonica.

14:01.170 --> 14:02.580
No, no.
They're great.

14:02.580 --> 14:05.540
Everything's great.
It's...

14:05.540 --> 14:07.460
It's just...

14:07.460 --> 14:09.080
this.

14:09.080 --> 14:10.170
Me?

14:10.170 --> 14:11.170
Eh --

14:11.170 --> 14:13.460
Katie,
as VP of Events,

14:13.460 --> 14:15.790
you are front and center
of this company.

14:15.790 --> 14:18.080
You need to...
look the part.

14:18.080 --> 14:19.420
I...

14:19.420 --> 14:21.830
If there's just
something we could do

14:21.830 --> 14:24.210
about the frowny parts
of your face.

14:24.210 --> 14:26.210
Kevin!

14:26.210 --> 14:27.960
Get in here.
I need another pair of hands.

14:27.960 --> 14:30.290
I'm sorry.

14:30.290 --> 14:31.380
I can't lose
this job.

14:31.380 --> 14:33.830
I owe $67,000
in student loans.

14:33.830 --> 14:35.380
Philosophy major.

14:35.380 --> 14:38.620
You can't Botox away
being an idiot, Kevin.

14:38.620 --> 14:40.670
Oh, God.

14:40.670 --> 14:44.330
♪♪

14:44.330 --> 14:47.710
Oliver, I'm sorry I haven't
been able to help you.

14:47.710 --> 14:48.790
I appreciate it,

14:48.790 --> 14:50.790
but there's nothing
anyone can do.

14:52.960 --> 14:55.670
Well,
I talked to Dr. Ellie --

14:55.670 --> 14:58.750
who I now call Eleanor since
I'm not in her class anymore.

14:58.750 --> 15:00.920
She doesn't
care for it --

15:00.920 --> 15:02.880
and she gave me some resources
that might help.

15:04.540 --> 15:07.080
"Are You
Being Bullied?"

15:07.080 --> 15:08.040
Nope.

15:11.080 --> 15:12.500
"How to Come Out
to Your Family"?

15:12.500 --> 15:13.420
Mm?

15:13.420 --> 15:14.880
No.

15:14.880 --> 15:16.580
"My Changing Body"?

15:16.580 --> 15:18.290
[ Scoffs ]
Too late.

15:21.290 --> 15:23.750
"Teen Help Line"?
Really?

15:23.750 --> 15:25.500
Dr. Ellie says
it's a hotline

15:25.500 --> 15:27.960
where teens can talk to other
teens about their problems.

15:27.960 --> 15:29.790
Not interested.

15:29.790 --> 15:31.380
Well, I certainly won't be
the last girl

15:31.380 --> 15:33.380
who thinks
she can fix you.

15:33.380 --> 15:35.380
I don't know the others,
but I pity them already.

15:35.380 --> 15:44.380
♪♪

15:44.380 --> 15:45.880
Ah, Katie.

15:45.880 --> 15:48.000
Tomorrow's party
is a boat christening,

15:48.000 --> 15:50.040
and I need
some noisy sea lions

15:50.040 --> 15:51.960
removed from
the marina --

15:51.960 --> 15:53.040
humanely.

15:53.040 --> 15:55.500
I'm kidding.
Do it any way you can.

15:55.500 --> 15:57.000
I'm on it,
Whitney.

15:58.330 --> 16:03.790
♪♪

16:03.790 --> 16:05.000
What are you
smiling about?

16:05.000 --> 16:06.460
♪♪

16:06.460 --> 16:08.830
This is why
you need Botox. See?

16:08.830 --> 16:12.000
Your face should not have
this much expression. [ Sighs ]

16:13.380 --> 16:15.000
What are you doing here?

16:15.000 --> 16:16.380
I wanted
to thank you.

16:16.380 --> 16:17.500
What you said last night
helped me realize

16:17.500 --> 16:19.710
something very important.
What did I say?

16:19.710 --> 16:21.790
You said that hating your job
was no big deal

16:21.790 --> 16:23.580
because everyone hates
their job, but you know what?

16:23.580 --> 16:25.960
I don't.
I actually love teaching.

16:25.960 --> 16:28.380
I am so happy
for you.

16:28.380 --> 16:30.380
Does this mean
you'll stop wearing the --
Not now.

16:30.380 --> 16:32.790
You supported me when I said
I wanted to mix things up,

16:32.790 --> 16:34.380
so guess what I did?

16:34.380 --> 16:36.170
I taught my class
outside today,

16:36.170 --> 16:37.330
and my students
loved it.

16:37.330 --> 16:39.210
That sounds so fun.

16:39.210 --> 16:41.620
I finally realized
the guy I am.

16:41.620 --> 16:44.420
I'm the guy who loves his job
and loves his family

16:44.420 --> 16:48.170
and wants his wife
to be as happy as he is.

16:51.040 --> 16:52.540
What about
the extra money?

16:52.540 --> 16:53.330
We'll make it work.

16:56.330 --> 16:57.380
Katie.

16:57.380 --> 16:59.710
I need you
at the marina right now.

16:59.710 --> 17:03.790
♪♪

17:03.790 --> 17:05.830
Sorry, Whitney.

17:05.830 --> 17:07.420
Move your own
damn sea lions!

17:07.420 --> 17:08.460
[ Scoffs ]

17:09.670 --> 17:10.670
Hit it, Greg!

17:10.670 --> 17:12.040
♪ Ow ♪

17:12.040 --> 17:13.750
[ Roni Lee's "Cherry Bomb"
plays ]

17:13.750 --> 17:17.420
♪ Yeah ♪

17:17.420 --> 17:21.290
♪ I'm your
ch-ch-ch-ch-ch-ch-cherry bomb ♪

17:21.290 --> 17:24.420
♪ Hello, world,
I'm your wild girl ♪

17:24.420 --> 17:27.670
♪ I'm your
ch-ch-ch-ch-ch-ch-cherry bomb ♪

17:27.670 --> 17:29.830
♪ Cherry bomb ♪

17:29.830 --> 17:31.670
♪ Cherry bomb ♪

17:31.670 --> 17:34.790
♪ Cherry bomb ♪

17:34.790 --> 17:36.920
I quit!

17:36.920 --> 17:39.120
♪♪

17:39.120 --> 17:40.500
It's just
how I imagined it.

17:40.500 --> 17:41.540
[ Chuckles ]

17:43.380 --> 17:44.960
[ Sighs ]
With Katie gone,

17:44.960 --> 17:46.210
maybe it's time
for you to step up.

17:46.210 --> 17:47.830
You mean
I can have her job?

17:47.830 --> 17:50.500
No, I mean
fix the ice sculpture.

17:50.500 --> 17:52.420
But --
Fix it, Kevin.

17:52.420 --> 17:54.580
Move it.

17:54.580 --> 18:02.460
♪♪

18:02.460 --> 18:05.960
Hey, you look like you're
in a good mood for a change.

18:05.960 --> 18:07.380
Did one of your IPOs
make a split

18:07.380 --> 18:08.830
into dividends
and then --

18:08.830 --> 18:10.000
Eh, forget it.

18:10.000 --> 18:11.500
I don't know
how money works.

18:11.500 --> 18:13.670
No, I just got off the phone
with Teen Help Line.

18:13.670 --> 18:15.000
You called?

18:15.000 --> 18:15.830
Did they help you
with your problem?

18:15.830 --> 18:16.960
They sure did.

18:16.960 --> 18:18.750
I'm proud of you.

18:18.750 --> 18:21.290
It's hard to be vulnerable,
reach out for help.

18:22.790 --> 18:25.540
And, of course, it's none of
the stuff I was just saying.

18:25.540 --> 18:27.170
What is going on,
Oliver?

18:27.170 --> 18:29.080
I just had
a very interesting conversation

18:29.080 --> 18:30.710
with one of
the counselors.

18:30.710 --> 18:32.790
He said a lot of the people
who volunteer there

18:32.790 --> 18:36.000
go on to top colleges,
including Harvard.

18:36.000 --> 18:39.120
But most importantly,
you'd be helping people.

18:39.120 --> 18:41.830
Anna-Kat, do you have a pamphlet
for hearing aids?

18:41.830 --> 18:43.380
Dad heard
"helping people"

18:43.380 --> 18:46.170
when I clearly said
"Harvard."

18:46.170 --> 18:48.580
[ Slowly ]
Harvard.

18:49.670 --> 18:51.540
[ Normal voice ]
And all I have to do
is apply and get in.

18:51.540 --> 18:53.790
And get this --
it's all done sitting down.

18:53.790 --> 18:55.790
Look at you,
Anna-Kat.

18:55.790 --> 18:57.750
You thought you couldn't
cheer us up, but you did.

18:57.750 --> 18:59.920
But there's someone else
who still needs my help.

18:59.920 --> 19:02.170
Let's talk about
the bracelet, Greg.

19:02.170 --> 19:04.500
♪♪

19:04.500 --> 19:05.710
Yeah.

19:07.290 --> 19:09.620
Goodbye,
fully functioning can opener.

19:09.620 --> 19:11.540
We can't
afford you anymore.

19:11.540 --> 19:13.750
Goodbye,
hand-crank pasta press.

19:13.750 --> 19:15.380
I knew you were just gonna
collect dust in the basement,

19:15.380 --> 19:16.620
but the idea of you
was enough.

19:16.620 --> 19:18.250
[ Chuckles ]

19:18.250 --> 19:20.330
Goodbye, cactus-shaped
margarita glasses.

19:20.330 --> 19:21.880
The fiesta's over.

19:21.880 --> 19:23.170
Mm.

19:23.170 --> 19:26.460
Goodbye,
banana hanger.

19:26.460 --> 19:28.580
And hello again,

19:28.580 --> 19:32.290
ceramic bowl
where fruit goes to die.

19:32.290 --> 19:33.580
[ Sighs ]

19:33.580 --> 19:34.790
Any regrets
about quitting?

19:34.790 --> 19:36.330
Hell, no.

19:36.330 --> 19:38.170
I know there's something better
for me out there.

19:38.170 --> 19:40.210
I want to find
what you have --

19:40.210 --> 19:43.580
a job that inspires me
and a smokin'-hot wife.

19:43.580 --> 19:45.290
[ Chuckles ]

19:49.540 --> 19:52.120
Greg: Are you sure
this is a good idea?

19:52.120 --> 19:53.500
[ Scoffs ] Are you kidding?
This is a great idea.

19:53.500 --> 19:55.580
If your students thought
having class outside was cool,

19:55.580 --> 19:56.920
they're gonna love this.

19:56.920 --> 19:58.540
Well, I am trying
to do new things.

19:58.540 --> 19:59.790
[ Scoffs ]

19:59.790 --> 20:02.120
Trust me,
it's gonna be awesome.

20:02.120 --> 20:04.670
Okay. You ready?
Let's hear it.

20:04.670 --> 20:08.420
[ As Abraham Lincoln ]
Four score and seven years ago,

20:08.420 --> 20:11.580
our fathers brought forth
on this continent

20:11.580 --> 20:15.420
a new nation,
conceived in liberty

20:15.420 --> 20:17.580
and dedicated
to the proposition

20:17.580 --> 20:20.750
that all men
are created equal.

20:20.750 --> 20:22.000
This is amazing.

20:22.000 --> 20:23.710
It's like history
come to life.

20:23.710 --> 20:27.420
Now we are engaged
in a great Civil War.

20:27.420 --> 20:28.960
Katie:
[ As Mary Todd Lincoln ] Abe?

20:28.960 --> 20:30.880
Abe, honey?

20:30.880 --> 20:32.960
Yes, Mary Todd?

20:32.960 --> 20:34.620
Do you want
to wrap this speech up?

20:34.620 --> 20:36.420
We're going to be late
to the theater.

20:36.420 --> 20:37.380
[ Inhales sharply ]

20:37.380 --> 20:39.380
I got us seats
in the balcony.

20:39.380 --> 20:40.670
[ Normal voice ]
That's not funny.

20:40.670 --> 20:42.250
Come on.

20:42.250 --> 20:44.120
Give us a kiss.

20:44.120 --> 20:45.420
No.
[ Smooching ]

20:45.420 --> 20:47.120
No!

20:47.120 --> 20:48.920
Mwah, mwah!

20:48.920 --> 20:50.380
[ Continues
smooching ]

20:50.380 --> 20:51.120
No!
